        <h2>
            <span class="h1-fs">
                <strong>Basics</strong>
            </span>
        </h2>
        <p style="text-align: justify;">You can access every installed App in your Odoo database on
            your main dashboard.</p>
        <ul>
            <li style="text-align: justify">
                <b>
                    <font class="text-o-color-1">Point of Sale App:</font>
                </b> Manage in-store transactions efficiently, handling sales of seeds, tools, and supplies with ease.
            </li>
            <li style="text-align: justify">
                <b>
                    <font class="text-o-color-1">Sales App:</font>
                </b> Handle B2B orders and contracts for large farming clients, ensuring accurate pricing.
            </li>
            <li style="text-align: justify">
                <b>
                    <font class="text-o-color-1">Purchase App:</font>
                </b> Streamline the procurement of farming products from suppliers, managing costs and lead times.
            </li>
            <li style="text-align: justify">
                <b>
                    <font class="text-o-color-1">eCommerce App:</font>
                </b> Expand your reach by selling products online, offering convenience to modern farmers.
            </li>
            <li style="text-align: justify">
                <b>
                    <font class="text-o-color-1">Website App:</font>
                </b>
                <font class="text-o-color-3"> Build a professional online presence to showcase your catalog and attract new customers.</font>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="o_editor_banner user-select-none lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-info pb-0 pt-3 o-contenteditable-false" data-oe-role="status" role="status">
            <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" data-oe-aria-label="Banner Info" aria-label="Banner Info">💡</i>
            <div class="w-100 px-3 o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true" contenteditable="true">
                <p style="text-align: justify;">Odoo is entirely integrated into an App. Download it
                    to <b>manage your entire business from your phone</b>.                    <s>
                        <br/>
                        </s>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p>
                <br/>
                </p>
                <h2 data-heading-link-id="461300383c2fe3cf">
                    <span class="h1-fs">
                        <strong>Activities</strong>
                    </span>
                    <br/>
                    </h2>
                    <p style="text-align: justify;">By uploading this module's demo data, your database has been
            filled with a few contacts.</p>
                    <p style="text-align: justify;">To get a rapid understanding of the processes this Odoo
            package offers, you can execute the following flows and configure the settings to suit
            your Agricultural Store.</p>
                    <p style="text-align: justify;">Of course, this is just an overview of the features included
            in this package. Feel free to add new apps, delete/modify demo data, and test everything
            around!</p>
                    <div data-oe-role="status" class="o_editor_banner user-select-none o-contenteditable-false lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-warning pb-0 pt-3" role="status">
                        <i data-oe-aria-label="Banner Warning" class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" aria-label="Banner Warning">⚠️</i>
                        <div class="o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true w-100 px-3" contenteditable="true">
                            <p>You didn't import demo data? You can still do it. Go to Apps &gt; Industries &gt;
                    Upgrade your Agricultural Shop package and select the
                    relevant checkbox</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <h3 data-heading-link-id="40ef2839a7e68378">
                            <br/>
                            </h3>
                        </ul>
                        <h3 data-heading-link-id="7b890df3b1cfaeed">
                            <span class="h2-fs">Manage your products️ 📦</span>
                        </h3>
                        <p style="text-align: justify;">Odoo enables complete control
            over your <b>product catalog</b> and<strong> basic </strong>
                            <b>stock management</b>, ensuring your inventory
            data is always accurate.</p>
                        <h4 style="text-align: justify;" data-heading-link-id="1ada604692adb7b3">
                            <u>Create and Categorize Products</u>
                        </h4>
                        <p style="text-align: justify;">Start by creating your products within the <b>Products</b>
            tab, filling in all necessary details. The system uses three distinct categories to
            provide maximum flexibility across your business:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                    <b>Product Category:</b> For internal tracking and
                    reporting.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                    <b>E-commerce Category:</b> For easier product
                    retrieval by customers on your online store.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                    <b>Point of Sale Category:</b> For organizing
                    transactions within your shop system.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                            <b>Key Product Settings:</b>
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">Accurately <b>update the inventoried quantity</b>.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">Decide whether to allow sales of <b>out-of-stock
                    products</b>.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">Define <b>product variants</b> for an improved
                    e-commerce customer journey. <i>Important: Only assign a single value per
                    attribute to prevent the system from creating separate stock entities.</i>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">
                 </p>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="o_editor_banner user-select-none o-contenteditable-false lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-success pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-role="status" role="status">
                            <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" data-oe-aria-label="Banner Success" aria-label="Banner Success">🚀</i>
                            <div class="o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true w-100 px-3" contenteditable="true">
                                <p>the current setup keeps things simple by using basic product counts to track stock. If you need more power, the <b>Inventory app</b> introduces advanced features like barcode scanning, location tracking, and serial number management.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <b>Note:</b> Increased capability leads to higher complexity and more maintenance.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <b>Our Advice:</b> Stick with your current streamlined configuration until you’re fully comfortable. When you're ready to upgrade, try the Inventory module on a duplicated database first to ensure it fits your workflow. 😉</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            <br/>
                            </p>
                            <h3 data-heading-link-id="d36eae9c3faa73be">
                                <span class="h2-fs">Selling in the Store 🛍️</span>
                            </h3>
                            <p>Odoo’s <strong>Point of Sale (POS)</strong> system ensures fast and smooth
            transactions in your agriculturalshop. Whether you sell individual packaged seeds,
            or bulk pick &amp; mix, Odoo has you covered.</p>
                            <div class="o_editor_banner user-select-none o-contenteditable-false lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-info pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-role="status" role="status">
                                <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" data-oe-aria-label="Banner Info" aria-label="Banner Info">💡</i>
                                <div class="o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true w-100 px-3" contenteditable="true">
                                    <p>Enable <strong>weight-based pricing</strong> for pick &amp; mix candy
                    by setting the unit of measure to <strong>grams or kilograms</strong> (Point
                    of Sale &gt; Three dot menu &gt; IoT Box &gt; Electronic Scale).</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                <strong>
                                    <u>Process</u>
                                </strong>
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li style="text-align: justify;">
                                    <strong></strong>To start an order in your Point of
                Sale (POS) session, scan or select all items. For products sold by weight (grams or
                kilograms), a window will pop up automatically. Enter the specific weight, and the
                final price will be calculated immediately.<br/></li>
                                </ul>
                                <div class="o_editor_banner user-select-none o-contenteditable-false lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-success pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-role="status" role="status">
                                    <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" data-oe-aria-label="Banner Success" aria-label="Banner Success">✅</i>
                                    <div class="o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true w-100 px-3" contenteditable="true">
                                        <p>For full automation, connect a scale to your POS system using
                    anIoT Box.</p>
                                        <p>
                    &#xFEFF;<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/sales/point_of_sale/pos_hardware.html">&#xFEFF; <span style="font-weight: normal;">🎓 Hardware</span> &#xFEFF;</a>&#xFEFF;</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <ul>
                                <li class="oe-nested">
                                    <p>
                                        <br/>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Accept multiple payment options: cash, card, and mobile payments.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Generate printed or digital receipts for customers.</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <div class="o_editor_banner user-select-none o-contenteditable-false lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-info pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-role="status" role="status">
                                    <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" data-oe-aria-label="Banner Info" aria-label="Banner Info">🚀</i>
                                    <div class="o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true w-100 px-3" contenteditable="true">
                                        <p>These tools allow you to manage your sales strategy and customer interactions
                    effectively:</p>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>
                                                    <b>Pricelist Segmentation:</b> Define multiple pricing structures for the
                            same product, supporting different business models (e.g., B2B vs. B2C)
                            and enabling <b>client-specific pricing contracts</b>.
                                                </p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>
                                                    <b>Promotional Agility:</b> Use <b>discounts and promotions</b> to
                            quickly adjust pricing for sales events or to give targeted, <b>manual
                            reductions</b> at the point of sale.</p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>
                                                    <b>Loyalty Programs:</b> Implement <b>loyalty cards</b> as a core
                            strategy to <b>activate customer retention</b> and increase lifetime
                            value.</p>
                                            </li>
                                        </ol>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <p>
            &#xFEFF;<a href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/sales/sales/products_prices/prices/pricing.html" class="btn btn-secondary">&#xFEFF; <span style="font-weight: normal;">🎓 Sales</span> &#xFEFF;</a>&#xFEFF;</p>
                            <h1 data-heading-link-id="6fb3eb0561f31975">
                                <br/>
                                </h1>
                                <h3 data-heading-link-id="98676227b2653bbc">
                                    <span class="h2-fs">Selling Online 💻️</span>
                                </h3>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">Your e-commerce setup involves three main areas: <b>Product
            Settings</b>,                                    <b>Website-Wide Settings</b>, and <b>Payment &amp; Delivery Methods</b>.
                                </p>
                                <h4 style="text-align: justify;" data-heading-link-id="3fc94dd1c9cfbaad">
                                    <u>1. Configure Products and Their Display</u>
                                </h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Publishing:</b> Each product can be <b>published
                    independently</b> on your online store.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Product-Level Settings:</b> Define core product
                    settings directly on the <b>product form</b>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Layout Settings:</b> Adjust the visual
                    presentation and layout of products using the <b>website editor</b>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 style="text-align: justify;" data-heading-link-id="385e5614aa5a497d">
                                    <u>2. Review General E-commerce Policies</u>
                                </h4>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">Navigate to <b>Website Settings</b> to configure
                    global e-commerce policies.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Crucial Review:</b> You must review all
                    e-commerce settings to ensure they align with your internal business policies
                    (e.g., when invoices are generated, whether a mandatory customer check-in is
                    required for ordering, etc.).</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <h4 style="text-align: justify;" data-heading-link-id="39ec640b48c084ba">
                                    <u>3. Set Up Payment and Delivery</u>
                                </h4>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">Use the <b>Website &gt; Configuration</b> menu to enable all
            your transaction options.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Payment Providers &amp; Methods:</b> Go to <b>Website
                    &gt; Configuration &gt; Payment Providers</b> and install <b>all</b> the payment
                    methods and providers you plan to offer (e.g., credit card processors, PayPal,
                    etc.).</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Delivery Methods:</b> Go to <b>Website &gt;
                    Configuration &gt; Delivery Methods</b> to define all available options and
                    their costs.</p>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>
                                                <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                                    <b>External Providers:</b> Check if a
                            predefined Odoo connection exists if you work with specific shipping
                            carriers.</p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                                    <b>In-Store Pickup (Click &amp; Collect):</b>
                            If you wish to offer this, you must <b>activate the setting</b> within
                            the <b>Website Settings</b> first.</p>
                                            </li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>
            &#xFEFF;<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/shipping_receiving/setup_configuration.html">&#xFEFF; <span style="font-weight: normal;">🎓 Delivery Methods</span> &#xFEFF;</a>&#xFEFF;</p>
                            <p>
                                <br/></p>
                                <h3 data-heading-link-id="856f05b198c3ec03">B2B Customer Configuration and Sales Workflow<span class="h2-fs">🤝</span>
                                </h3>
                                <p>Use these settings to tailor the experience for your B2B clients:</p>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Define B2B Pricing:</b> Create and assign a <b>dedicated
                    pricelist</b> to each B2B contact. Ensure this pricelist is active on your
                    website so the customer sees their agreed-upon prices upon login.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Capture Requests:</b> Any submission via the <b>"Contact
                    Us"</b> page instantly generates a new <b>CRM opportunity</b>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Qualify Leads:</b> Engage with the client through
                    the CRM opportunity to fully understand their request—whether it's a need for a
                    specific product, a supplier inquiry, or general information.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Quote and Confirm:</b> If a specific demand
                    requires pricing, generate a <b>quotation directly from the opportunity</b>. The
                    client can then <b>confirm and sign it online</b>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Automatic Delivery:</b> Once the quote is
                    accepted, it's possible to deliver the products just
                    as it does for a regular e-commerce order.</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                                <p style="text-align: justify;">
            &#xFEFF;<a href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/sales/crm.html" class="btn btn-secondary">&#xFEFF; <span style="font-weight: normal;">🎓 CRM</span> &#xFEFF;</a>&#xFEFF;</p>
                            <div class="o_editor_banner user-select-none o-contenteditable-false lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-success pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-role="status" role="status">
                                <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal" data-oe-aria-label="Banner Success" aria-label="Banner Success">✅</i>
                                <div class="o_editor_banner_content o-contenteditable-true w-100 px-3" contenteditable="true">
                                    <p>You have flexibility regarding when to generate invoices:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>You can choose in the settings to <b>invoice either before or after
                            delivery</b>.
                                            </p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>You also have the option to require a <b>down payment</b> initially, with
                            the remainder invoiced later.</p>
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                <br/>
                                </p>
                                <h3 style="text-align: justify;" data-heading-link-id="f8f4f71a840ebd1b">
                                    <span class="h2-fs">Manage your website 🌐</span>
                                </h3>
                                <p>You can easily tailor your website to provide the information you want for potential
